msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gladiator.md:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Armor Class** 16 (studded leather, shield)    \n"
"**Hit Points** 112 (15d8 + 45)    \n"
"**Speed** 30 ft. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gladiator.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| STR     | DEX     | CON     | INT     | WIS     | CHA     |\n"
"|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|---------|\n"
"| 18 (+4) | 15 (+2) | 16 (+3) | 10 (+0) | 12 (+1) | 15 (+2) |   \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gladiator.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Saving Throws** Str +7, Dex +5, Con +6    \n"
"**Skills** Athletics +10, Intimidation +5    \n"
"**Senses** passive Perception 11    \n"
"**Languages** any one language (usually Common)    \n"
"**Challenge** 5 (1,800 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gladiator.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Brave.** The gladiator has advantage on saving throws against being "
"frightened.    \n"
"**Brute.** A melee weapon deals one extra die of its damage when the "
"gladiator hits with it (included in the attack). \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gladiator.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Actions \n"
"**Multiattack.** The gladiator makes three melee attacks or two ranged "
"attacks.    \n"
"**Spear.** _Melee or _Ranged Weapon Attack:__ +7 to hit, reach 5 ft. and "
"range 20/60 ft., one target. _Hit:_ 11 (2d6 + 4) piercing damage, or 13 (2d8 "
"+ 4) piercing damage if used with two hands to make a melee attack.    \n"
"**Shield Bash.** _Melee Weapon Attack:_ +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one "
"creature. _Hit:_ 9 (2d4 + 4) bludgeoning damage. If the target is a Medium "
"or smaller creature, it must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw or be "
"knocked prone. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gladiator.md:32
msgid ""
"### Reactions **Parry.** The gladiator adds 3 to its AC against one melee "
"attack that would hit it. To do so, the gladiator must see the attacker and "
"be wielding a melee weapon."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/gladiator.md:34
msgid ""
"### Description Gladiators battle for the entertainment of raucous "
"crowds. Some gladiators are brutal pit fighters who treat each match as a "
"life-or-death struggle, while others are professional duelists who command "
"huge fees but rarely fight to the death."
msgstr ""
